<Author>MaximillianAmsterdam
<Content>Acceptable experience I've stayed in the Apollofirst hotel for three nights during Oktober 2006.Appolofirst is located in the best part of Amsterdam; Oud-Zuid.Not in the center but in a nice residence with wealthy locals and some tourists.The Appolofirst is housed in an authentic building which is typical for Amsterdam.The reception is small but cosy ,the staff is polite and do the best they can. The rooms are mediumsized and are decorated in a sort of authentic style. The rooms offer a average bed and a little place to sit. A workdesk is provided. The lightening was below average, not very special. The bathroom is large and clean and gives you a wealthy feeling. Unfortunately the rooms aren't very soundproof.In my opinion this hotel is very suitable for traveller's who like to stay in a quiet and very lovely area not far from Amsterdam's main hotspots where they can blend with the locals.Overall; a pretty nice place to stay, not very special but worth the money. 
