<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Hotel I stayed at the Apollofirst for four nights with a friend of mine in June 2005 and we really enjoyed it. The room was clean, and the bathroom was HUGE!! The price of our room included breakfast, which was a buffet each morning. The breakfast had a great selection of hot and cold food. The staff was VERY nice and helpful. The location of the hotel is about a 10-minute walk to the museum area. There is a Tram #5, which is right at the end of the block (2-minute walk) which goes to Central Station and just about everywhere in the city. The hotel also has a great little bar area to relax and have a drink or read. It is very quite and away from the hustle and bustle. It is an older hotel, but I liked its classic charm. I would stay there again if I were in Amsterdam. 
